1
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:51,920
Unethical doctor assaults patient's family in public

2
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:53,600
Where's the justice in this society?

3
00:00:53,759 --> 00:00:54,719
Where's the fairness?

4
00:00:55,920 --> 00:00:56,960
Rich people's lives matter,

5
00:00:57,320 --> 00:00:58,759
Is my daughter's life worth nothing?

6
00:00:59,079 --> 00:00:59,600
Let go!

7
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:00,439
Stop making a scene here.

8
00:01:00,520 --> 00:01:01,320
Get him out of here, now!

9
00:01:01,320 --> 00:01:02,240
Either apologize publicly,

10
00:01:02,359 --> 00:01:03,039
or face suspension.

11
00:01:03,359 --> 00:01:04,400
Don't you dare cause trouble

12
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:05,439
for me at a time like this.

13
00:01:06,599 --> 00:01:07,760
Dr. Jiang seems cold but he's kind-hearted.

14
00:01:07,879 --> 00:01:09,400
We all believe he's not that kind of person.

15
00:01:09,719 --> 00:01:10,760
There must be some misunderstanding here.

16
00:01:10,879 --> 00:01:11,519
Jiang Tiancai!

17
00:01:11,920 --> 00:01:13,079
Why won't you explain yourself?

18
00:01:13,519 --> 00:01:14,680
Don't you know that leaving now

19
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:15,840
means destroying your own future?

20
00:01:16,239 --> 00:01:17,120
I've graduated.

21
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:18,439
I'm coming back this month.

22
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,079
Can we meet?

23
00:01:20,319 --> 00:01:22,480
That family member clearly started it.

24
00:01:22,719 --> 00:01:24,840
Why should Jiang Tiancai take the fall?

25
00:01:24,959 --> 00:01:26,959
That doctor must've done something shady.

26
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:29,000
Otherwise, why would he run off so fast?

27
00:01:30,319 --> 00:01:31,239
If Pingjin won't keep him,

28
00:01:31,280 --> 00:01:32,200
somewhere else will.

29
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:33,040
Bro,

30
00:01:33,359 --> 00:01:34,799
as long as you don't mind our humble clinic,

31
00:01:35,079 --> 00:01:35,680
once you come here,

32
00:01:35,840 --> 00:01:37,439
you'll be Maxillofacial Surgery's Deputy Chief.

33
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:06,000
Notify Dr. Chen, hurry!

34
00:02:07,879 --> 00:02:08,479
Slow down.

35
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:10,120
Hurry, this way!

36
00:02:12,919 --> 00:02:13,400
Hurry!

37
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:15,039
Move aside!

38
00:02:24,719 --> 00:02:25,919
Tang Yi, aren't you off today?

39
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:26,680
What's going on?

40
00:02:26,759 --> 00:02:27,759
A fall victim I happened to come across.

41
00:02:28,039 --> 00:02:29,439
Get Dr. Chen down here for a consult.

42
00:02:29,479 --> 00:02:30,080
Got it.

43
00:02:35,719 --> 00:02:37,360
Wake up, can you hear me?

44
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:38,680
Any dizziness or chest pain?

45
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:39,800
Can you move your hands and feet?

46
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:43,080
Don't fall asleep, stay with me!

47
00:02:44,759 --> 00:02:45,520
Your hand!

48
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:46,719
Just disinfect it, it's fine.

49
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:47,719
Tend to the patient first.

50
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:49,039
Let me bandage it for you.

51
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:50,520
It's fine, focus on the patient.

52
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:59,360
Soft tissue laceration on the face.

53
00:03:05,759 --> 00:03:07,159
Suction, quickly!

54
00:03:08,479 --> 00:03:09,199
Here.

55
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,159
Now I finally understand

56
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:13,199
why pediatric dentistry has it good.

57
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:14,719
At least we don't face scenes this bloody.

58
00:03:14,759 --> 00:03:15,919
Cut the chatter, open his mouth.

59
00:03:16,879 --> 00:03:17,520
Here.

60
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:25,280
Intraoral mucosal tear.

61
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:26,840
Hematoma on the floor of the mouth.

62
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:28,319
Tongue is elevated.

63
00:03:29,759 --> 00:03:31,520
Alveolar fracture involving teeth 46 and 47.

64
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,000
Send him for a CT first.

65
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:35,039
Blood oxygen has dropped to 88.

66
00:03:47,319 --> 00:03:49,479
I'm with Maxillofacial Surgery at Pingjin First Hospital.

67
00:04:02,039 --> 00:04:04,199
Tongue prolapse from progressive hematoma

68
00:04:04,439 --> 00:04:05,240
is causing airway obstruction.

69
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:08,240
By the time the imaging comes back,

70
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:10,080
we'll be calling time of death.

71
00:04:10,479 --> 00:04:11,240
Don't tell me you're...

72
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:12,560
Dexamethasone, 10mg IV push.

73
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:13,840
Switch to a smaller bronchoscope.

74
00:04:27,439 --> 00:04:28,160
What's the blood oxygen?

75
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:29,680
Blood oxygen at 90 percent.

76
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:31,360
Sorry, I just got out of surgery.

77
00:04:31,519 --> 00:04:32,240
What's the situation?

78
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:33,560
Support his jaw.

79
00:04:35,319 --> 00:04:36,720
Prepare for interdental wiring.

80
00:05:05,879 --> 00:05:07,199
Blood oxygen at 94 percent.

81
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:09,600
We can send him for a CT now.

82
00:05:28,639 --> 00:05:30,319
Skull, cervical spine, chest, and abdomen all normal.

83
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:32,240
Open, multiple fractures of the mandible,

84
00:05:32,439 --> 00:05:33,600
with soft tissue entrapment.

85
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:36,040
The situation's actually better than expected.

86
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:37,519
So can we operate now?

87
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:40,160
Bilateral mandibular angle fractures,

88
00:05:40,279 --> 00:05:41,560
with comminution of the symphysis.

89
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:43,879
But the suprahyoid muscle attachments are intact.

90
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,560
Operating now would enlarge the trauma area.

91
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:48,759
Unstable, multiple fractures.

92
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,120
We must reliably restore mandibular continuity.

93
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:54,680
If the fracture ends shift,

94
00:05:54,959 --> 00:05:56,759
causing further soft tissue damage

95
00:05:57,160 --> 00:05:58,079
and worsening the hematoma,

96
00:05:58,759 --> 00:06:01,240
the patient could die from asphyxiation.

97
00:06:02,319 --> 00:06:04,279
The oxygenation index is barely above critical.

98
00:06:04,639 --> 00:06:06,360
Intraoperative flap elevation will worsen edema.

99
00:06:07,439 --> 00:06:09,120
An Attending Physician from a major hospital

100
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:11,519
should at least know that much, right?

101
00:06:13,319 --> 00:06:16,079
Intraoperative edema can still be controlled.

102
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:18,560
But every millimeter the fracture ends move now,

103
00:06:18,879 --> 00:06:20,959
the hematoma takes up 5ml of the airway.

104
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:22,720
Did your gym teacher teach you math?

105
00:06:23,439 --> 00:06:24,720
You can't even do simple math?

106
00:06:26,199 --> 00:06:27,079
Everyone's here.

107
00:06:27,959 --> 00:06:29,879
Guess I don't need to introduce you all.

108
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:31,079
Mentor.

109
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,639
If we operate now,

110
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:33,959
the probability of intraoperative risk...

111
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,720
No matter how high the intraoperative risk,

112
00:06:36,279 --> 00:06:37,959
it can't exceed the risk of asphyxiation.

113
00:06:38,519 --> 00:06:39,759
I agree with Dr. Jiang's judgment.

114
00:06:40,319 --> 00:06:41,040
Prepare for surgery.

115
00:07:10,079 --> 00:07:11,199
The tissue is fully exposed.

116
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:12,480
Here's a practical question for you.

117
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:14,480
Comminuted fracture of the mandibular angle,

118
00:07:14,839 --> 00:07:16,240
complete severance of the inferior alveolar nerve,

119
00:07:16,439 --> 00:07:17,519
and disrupted occlusal function.

120
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,279
How do you, in a single operation,

121
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:21,319
preserve both nerve function and occlusion?

122
00:07:21,439 --> 00:07:22,399
Epineurial suture,

123
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:24,480
plus a 3D occlusal guide to reposition fragments,

124
00:07:24,839 --> 00:07:26,319
Titanium plate fixation with trans-neural suspension.

125
00:07:27,759 --> 00:07:29,160
Pretty high sync rate, huh.

126
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:31,040
Interesting.

127
00:07:34,639 --> 00:07:36,800
That approach will damage the mental nerve.

128
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:39,120
See this 45-degree bevel?

129
00:07:39,839 --> 00:07:41,240
Dissect along the left side.

130
00:07:41,519 --> 00:07:42,720
That's at least 30 seconds faster

131
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:44,560
than what the textbook teaches you.

132
00:07:45,759 --> 00:07:46,600
Continue dissecting.

133
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:09,720
Perfect.

134
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:10,959
Mentor, you can wrap up.

135
00:08:11,279 --> 00:08:11,839
I'll handle the rest.

136
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,839
The mandibular ramus fracture has displaced posteriorly.

137
00:08:14,399 --> 00:08:15,720
It may have damaged the facial nerve.

138
00:08:16,199 --> 00:08:17,600
Sure you don't want to explore further?

139
00:08:20,959 --> 00:08:21,720
What do you think?

140
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:23,319
I...

141
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:24,920
You couldn't have overlooked

142
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,839
the possibility of facial nerve damage.

143
00:08:30,199 --> 00:08:31,000
You two, switch places.

144
00:08:31,279 --> 00:08:32,120
Continue the surgery.

145
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:57,919
Saturday won't work anymore.

146
00:08:58,080 --> 00:08:59,200
Would Monday work for you?

147
00:09:00,559 --> 00:09:01,080
Okay.

148
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:02,519
Then I'll book it for you.

149
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:03,720
Alright.

150
00:09:03,799 --> 00:09:05,240
Little Qiao, busy as ever?

151
00:09:05,559 --> 00:09:06,200
All set!

152
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:08,159
That new Dr. Jiang at our hospital,

153
00:09:08,279 --> 00:09:09,200
have you heard about him?

154
00:09:11,519 --> 00:09:12,320
Have you heard?

155
00:09:14,519 --> 00:09:16,360
The most legendary Attending Physician

156
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:18,039
of Pingjin First Hospital's Maxillofacial Surgery.

157
00:09:18,279 --> 00:09:20,159
His surgery success rate ranks first in the department,

158
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,799
but his outpatient complaint rate is highest in the hospital.

159
00:09:23,399 --> 00:09:25,000
Arrogant, aloof, and cold-hearted.

160
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:25,879
What?

161
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,759
Dr. Pei wants to follow in his footsteps?

162
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:28,840
Look at you.

163
00:09:29,919 --> 00:09:31,720
Your taste in men really is off.

164
00:09:31,919 --> 00:09:33,279
I actually think Dr. Jiang

165
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:35,360
is suave, free-spirited, and capable.

166
00:09:36,559 --> 00:09:38,360
A million times better than

167
00:09:38,799 --> 00:09:39,840
that petty Dr. Chen.

168
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:41,559
You—say one more word about Dr. Chen.

169
00:09:42,279 --> 00:09:43,559
You're such a violent woman,

170
00:09:43,759 --> 00:09:45,240
nobody but me would dare date you.

171
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:51,639
Dr. Tang, Dr. Tang.

172
00:09:53,559 --> 00:09:54,799
Dr. Tang, what do you think?

173
00:09:56,039 --> 00:09:56,720
About what?

174
00:09:57,399 --> 00:09:58,960
That new doctor who arrived today.

175
00:09:59,399 --> 00:10:00,559
He was still in the ER today—

176
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:03,759
What happened to your hand?

177
00:10:04,679 --> 00:10:05,200
It's nothing.

178
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:07,600
Must've gotten cut bringing the patient in.

179
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,480
It's fine, I'll go change the dressing.
